## What this workspace is

This directory is an **umbrella workspace** that hosts N git sub-repositories
under `repos/`. The list of sub-repos is declared in `repositories.json` at the
workspace root. Each sub-repo keeps its own `.git` directory — the workspace
itself does not contain their code directly.

## Managing sub-repos

- `repositories.json` — manifest of the sub-repos (name, url, path, branch,
  status). Only entries with `"status": "active"` are processed by the scripts.
- `./scripts/clone-all.sh` (or `.ps1`) — bootstrap: clones every active sub-repo
  into `repos/<path>/`. Safe to re-run; already-cloned repos are skipped.
- `./scripts/switch-branch.sh <branch>` (or `.ps1 -BranchName <branch>`) — aligns
  every active sub-repo onto the same branch. Uncommitted changes are auto-stashed.
- `./scripts/pull-all.sh` (or `.ps1`) — `git pull --ff-only` across all active sub-repos.

## VibeKanban compatibility

Keeping every sub-repo on the same branch (via `switch-branch`) makes tools like
VibeKanban treat the workspace as a single unit of work — one branch, many repos,
one task.

## Workspace-centric skills policy

The `.claude/skills/` tree lives **only at workspace root**. Open the workspace
root in Claude Code / Copilot / etc. and every bundled skill (including Polly,
the NONoise SDLC orchestrator) is available.

Sub-repos under `repos/` are plain code repositories and do **not** carry their
own skill tree. If you genuinely need skills inside a specific sub-repo, copy
the `.claude/` folder manually — NONoise ships workspace-centric by default.

## Project structure

- `repositories.json` — sub-repo manifest (workspace root)
- `scripts/` — `clone-all`, `switch-branch`, `pull-all` (`.sh` + `.ps1`)
- `repos/` — sub-repositories land here after `clone-all`
- `docs/` — architecture, requirements, PRD, sprints, calls, support
- `tools/` — workspace-level utilities

Application code lives inside each sub-repo under `repos/<name>/`, **not** at
the workspace root. There is no workspace-level `src/` by design.

